column3:
“Bless me Father, for I have sinned.  I purchased a 1/2 oz. of Cookies Kush, however my dispensary call it, Golden Cookies, but no matter the regional nomenclature, this batch of Cookies SC Lab tested in at 30.28% THC.
That's a cookie, baby, that one must taste, for it is so sweet, that it is easy to want that next puff.  But wait, I say wait!  Savor one good bong load, or one good puff off a nice joint or pipe load a...”

“This was some pretty strong stuff. A few puffs from my vaporizer and I was glued to the couch, virtually unable to budge for hours. After about two hours, it completely knocked me out and I woke up as the movie I had just started was ending. For as strong as the high was, it didn't mess with my brain too much and I was mostly just relaxed as I tried to watch movies with my wife.

There are two reasons that I don't gi...”
“I can't tell you this is a strong weed, cause that is an understatement. It had me nearly unable to carry on a conversation and/or move for about 4 hours. so yeah....”

“Tried this strain at Barney's Coffeeshop in Amsterdam and real talk, it was quit a treat. Cookies Cush resembles aromas found in Girl Scout Cookies. Although listed as an indica the effects touch close to a sativa dominate strain. Truly one of the better strains I tried.”
“Beautiful, delish, potent Indica. GrandDaddy Purple still takes the cake as my fave indica but Cookies Kush is a close second. Relaxing,  mellow, zero anxiety, some creativeness, top 10 faves.”

“I've been smoking on some cookies kush for a little over a month now and it's the perfect strain to smoke before bed 😍 I've been smoking for awhile, but take like 4 bong rips of this and it knocks me on my ass. Really, really, really strong indica hybrid, it's an amazing physical & head high. Great strain to smoke socially, everyone gets super baked super quick. 5/5 stars, will be picking up again!❤️”

“Note: Review for OG Cookies. Very relaxing body high followed by gradually intensifying cerebral effects. Great for pain management or just lounging around after a hard day's work. Sweet and pungent taste and aroma only lasts the first few hits.”

“Being born and raised in California, I have a big ol' soft spot for OG Kush. And who doesn't like Cookie strains?? So I had high hopes for this particular strain, as I lovvvvve Indicas especially, and I gotta say, it surpassed my wildest dreams!

Just a single big fat (1.4g) doobie rolled with a king size Juicy Jay Mango flavored rolling paper, and I fell head over heels for this stuff! 

Genuinely impressed by this ...”

“Not what I expected from a cross between GSC and OGK. It is a very nice strain. But when I think GSC or OGK, I think happy, giggly, uplifting, etc. This is very heavy in the face. It certainly has the calming effects. 

Maybe since I experienced this in a dab it was a bit heavy.  It's worth a try. Plenty of worse strains out there.”

“A sweet tasty strain for those who don't like too sacrifice potency for flavour this is you all over. It's sweet but retains that Kush element which gives a strong taste with strong effects. A good evening smoke if suffering from insomnia etc.”

“Method: Barney's Flower in a Vaporizer

Aroma: It smells, sweet with a bit of spice and fruit. 1/1 Star.
Taste: The sweet takes over at first with a marshmellow-y pastry taste before ending with some berry hints. I think this would be amazing as a vape cartridge to really pull out the right terpenes. 1.5/2 Stars.
Feel: A strong and classic indica. Had to cancel a walking tour I had later that night and just sit on a ...”
“Didn't realize I had the illustrious Cookies Kush till I was packing a bowl and realized the bud tender wrote Kush Cookies" a simple misspell. A real treat
column5: great for night night sleepy time.”"

column3: “Pretty intense. I couldn’t keep my mind from reflecting on my inner self. Great times and deep revelations.”

“I haven't been on leafly in a while, but have grown a number of new to me strains over the winter. I'll start here. I really like this strain. For the personal stuff, I like that it is an evening relaxing strain, but without knocking me to the floor or couch. I did a few more things before calling it a night. I just felt cozy and relaxed, and slept very well the whole night. Properly cured, she smells and tastes grea...”

“First strain I smoked in Amsterdam when I visited there with my ex. Being a great fan of the infamous Girl Scout Cookies, I just had to try out this one. And boy... it hit me hard. Never was that high after just one spliff. Very psychedelic, funky and relaxing. Will definitely buy this again when I visit the Dam this year in order to find out if it's still that good haha”

“Not a beginner strain or a strain for someone who doesn't smoke often.

I smoked a pre-rolled blunt  at Barney's Farm in Amsterdam.

The high started off as mellow but slowly escalated to the point where my heart was racing and I was sweating uncontrollably.  Took roughly two hours before I came down, but I slept like a baby on my 10 hour flight.”

“I haven't been on leafly in a while, but have grown a number of new to me strains over the winter. I'll start here. I really like this strain. For the personal stuff, I like that it is an evening relaxing strain, but without knocking me to the floor or couch. I did a few more things before calling it a night. I just felt cozy and relaxed, and slept very well the whole night. Properly cured, she smells and tastes grea...”

“Definitely a strain that kicks insomnia and depression in the butt! Cookies Kush is a smoke that allows you to sink into deep relaxation and sleep. Smoke a little bit less and just lay on your couch and be ridiculously happy! While Cookies Kush is one of the weaker strains I tried, it is one that I loved so much I hope to grow one day. Cookies Kush has allowed me to stop taking my sleeping medicine, and has helped to...”
“I just finished growing this plant it was extremely tall and loved an acidic feeding ph. was around 5.4 to 5.8 over all very good smoke with chucky buds. Next time I'll definitely top this plant.”

“Pretty good shit. Hits nice and smoothly, and has a very sweet smell to it. When smoking, one can really smell the sweetness (think savory, like sausages). Smoked a joint of this stuff and I'm experiencing a nice relaxed stone. Feeling a little spacey, kinda giggly, very hungry. If you want to just chill out for six hours and rediscover the wonders of tasty food, Cookies Kush is a real treat.”
“Really strong and earthy and gives off a lot of kief. The only thing is that it makes you EXTREMELY hungry”

“Very nice strain with one of the happiest highs I’ve ever been on. Spent my time playing games and browsing the web and everything was amazing. Definitely a nighttime strain though, it’ll make you want to sleep. Only reason it isnt five stars is because it did take me a fair bit to get more than a slight buzz.”

“When you cross breed two amazing strains your bound to create something magical.  Immediately after the first toke, you go into full meltdown. With a pungent aroma but a sweet after taste, your left to gaze at the clouds.”

“Deliciously stoned and a little trippy too. I'm a great lover of The Couchlock and always looking for something that'll glue me down. One of my favorites has been Afghan Kush, but that one is a bit more gloomy emotionally. Cookies Kush is a sweet, serene and joyous high with a serious couchlock and pretty tripping in the first moments it hits you. I am in love.”
“Really strong and earthy and gives off a lot of kief. The only thing is that it makes you EXTREMELY hungry”
“Shit got me stoned asf”

“in the middle growing this strain now, 58 days flower and im on day 40. nice dense crystally buds. guy who says it smells like barf and cheese got it right, although I had this strain plenty of times before I started growing it and ive always said it smells like mango and cheese, yeah it definitely smells like mango and cheese. not a dank smelling strain day 40 in flower like I thought kush was, but its a pleasant pu...”

“just perfect. the high was the right lullaby to put me to sleep. I haven't slept like I did on this strain.
this is a strain you don't wanna pass on.!!”

“All I can say is goodnight✌️🌛😴 Every time I smoked this strain I had to take a nap. Messed around and tried to wake n bake it once wound up putting my ass right back to sleep for another few hours. Definitely recommend for night time I'd say an hour before you plan on going to bed.”
“Great strain all around end product is amazing og took over on this one though huge kola buds with a fruity / baked goods smell”

“Early review:
Purchased Feminized 🌰🌰🌰 from Barney's Farm directly, shipped from 🇱🇺 to 🇺🇸, arrived safely in less than 2 weeks.
These were a little tough to germinate, lost a few but some have made it to vegetative state.

Smoke report probably February or March 2017”
“great for anxiety and stress... definitely night time use...”
“Great strain all around end product is amazing og took over on this one though huge kola buds with a fruity / baked goods smell”

“This review applies to a distillate cart by Liberty of Maryland. Technically the label is Cookies Kush #5. Not sure what the diff is. Anyway I got this for sleep, and it does help with that when I am tired. But I also enjoy it during the day as it works well on pain and makes me happy and relaxed and smiley 😀😀I’ve bought this particular cart twice now and will buy it again”
“great high smoked it awhile back a new cross breed has me to high to remember much but not too rough to hold it in”

“massive indica dominant fan here. I had this strain over in Amsterdam and it was lovely. I suffer with stress, anxiety and arthritis and this strain took the edge off all of these. Sativa's make me very anxious so if you're like me then this is a must go to indica whenever possible. lovely tasting bud. top marks”

“I just smoked about 3 bowls of some tree from Encanto called ‘OG Cookies’ and I figured the parent strains to be a phenotype of og Kush and GSC but will have to confirm. Effects are strong and still somewhat peaked/growing after an hour. Definite body-high and couch lock, also somewhat heady, but not anxiously so. Overall great aroma: heavy berry smell, light pine and light skunk smell. A VERY good tasting strain: si...”

“So far so great 😂 I have a full female in three weeks flower not a sign of male sacks anywhere... At least for the time being, but all you haters talking about males or hermies you must not grow much so I don't feel sorry for your sucky experience with this strain 💯🇺🇸”
“Didn't think I'd find anything better than GSC.  But this is!! 💜”
“Shit got me stoned asf”

“Vaped this with the volcano at Barneys!!!  Very very mello, chill, clear headed body high.  I would not recommend this for daytime use.  If you can’t sleep suffering from 🛫🛬 lag some of this 🍪🍪🍪🍪 Kush will do the trick.  🇳🇱🇳🇱🇳🇱🇳🇱🇳🇱 always a good time!!”
“as yet uncured, it's got a nice taste, earthy with a hint of mint. Relaxing high, not quite a sleeper but I'm sure when cured it will improve . overall not bad for pain even now.”
“Pretty nice high and helps a lot with my crohns. Only complaint is that it seems to give me pretty bad headaches. It might just be me but idk.”

“The sweetiest strain ever smoked. Tried it ar barney's lounge in Amsterdam. The taste is sweet and intense but not enough to just give up smoking it. It hitted slowly, it became stronger and stronger. A strong body relaxation and it sets your mind just right. I suffer of BPD and this strain got me like a high dose of benzos, I had full control on my feelings and no sense of guilty”

“Really fun strain to enjoy with some coffee and conversation. This one may keep you glued to the couch physically, but this is a fun head high, and you’ll be waxing poetic in no time. Also, munchies weren’t too bad with this one! I was thirsty, but wasn’t super enticed by food like I usually am with standard middies.”
“first time i smoked it this damn near knocked me tf out and i couldnt even get and but when i did i felt like i woke up on pluto but eventually youll be able to controll the high”

“This strain is very strong*.  
It blows away any previous high like a grenade exploding in the room.  
You end up one hit into a bubbler bowl, looking at your toes and forgetting what... how... you, who? got there. 
 
*I grow weed for a living.”
“This strain is Really good, it makes you feel calm and relaxed and it kinda takes you out of your mind but not into deep thought.”
“Got the taste of cookies during the high as opposed to the regular green apple.”
“Got the taste of cookies during the high as opposed to the regular green apple.”
“Was pleasantly surprised by how strong of an indica this strain was. The Buds were beautiful and full of sparkle. Mine tested out at 22% total cannaboids and was from the farm Gabriel”
“This was a great strain, had this in Amsterdam on my travels as well, was great before a bike ride”
“love it it’s nice and purple and decently hard hitting and doesn’t give you much cotton mouth”

“Pleasantly surprised with this one! Was skeptical of it due to the fact i don't really trust the Rollex phenotype of OG crossed with a Girl Scout, coming from Amsterdam (I do trust DNA however). Especially considering the fact that Barneys Farm won an award for Sweet Tooth, but it isn't even the real one. Anyhow this is some very pungent, sweet and stanky herb. U can taste and feel the Girl Scout but it isn't dominan...”

“Oh my god. Some of the most potent shit I’ve smoked, if not the most potent. Half of a bowl of cookies kush has me as high as a joint of blue dream would get me. Shit is strong, the taste is sweet af, and so is the smell. Definitely recommend this strain, only negative is you get a really dry mouth.”

“Very strong Weed with very sweet flavour. The buds are really compact and full of resin with a violet and dark green colors. The taste remember flower and berries. This plant is indica dominant and the stone comfirm it.
Raccomandata!”

“Having spent the last 12weeks growing out a few c/k indoors in the U.K. I'm happy to say the ladies are ready!
I thought it only right to review this strain whilst in the middle of smoking a nice joint, however I feel I should hurry my words in case I loose the power of thought and speech any time soon!😂
This strain has some complex flavours ! And is a joy on the pallet ! Not to mention the body and mind! It's certa...”

“Very strong Weed with very sweet flavour. The buds are really compact and full of resin with a violet and dark green colors. The taste remember flower and berries. This plant is indica dominant and the stone comfirm it.
Raccomandata!”

“COUCH. Nothing else is possible. NOTHING

As long as you understand that, it’s a 5 star strain.”

Overall great after work strain. After all it gave me the idea to sign up on here an...”

Increíble para un día que quieras experimentar en la comodidad de tu hogar. 

Definitivamente me puso feliz.”

“very hard hitting & taste good. stinky.  best strain of the October month so far”

“Grew this strain out 2 times, had no issues with males or hermie, 1 round with organic, 1 round synthetic...the organic was much better, how ever neither one of the grows put out top shelf, smell is earthy, cheese....very calming high, instant anxiety relief, but short duration and not potent at all”

“I really enjoyed this bud, lasts for hours, I'm tired and relaxed, my areas of pain are numb and I am giggling a lot. Very tasty bud, hint's of  sweetness with an earthy base.  The couch lock, cotton mouth, and munchies are real though.”
“its a very good strain very sweet tasting to me and half in to smoking it got to be very relaxing and a tad bit paranoid”

“very strong strain!
beginners go slow on it.
although indica dominant (very relaxing), its not the best strain to sleep with, as you can feel its sativa influence (mind stimulating). great high. 
smalls very much like coffee/bakery...and in the after taste you can see why they call it cookies!
great strain!”
“Nice indica strain, smells and tastes amazing, very sweet sugary taste. Severe couch lock was stuck to my sofa for a couple of hours. 8.5/10.”
“Great strain smells and taste good”
“My favorite. This strain had me laughing and clapping and feeling lovely. Handled my stress immediately, and I basically felt great.”

After eating my take out, I was like, nah, I'm going to chill. One more from the bowl & to sleep I went. After effects this Kush is a heavy hitter. Not for the faint at heart.”

“very relaxed and calm. I really enjoyed the high”
“Indica for really indicalovers perfekt cookie's spicy smell”

“This strain is in my top 5, a euphoria comes on, leaving you carefree, while engaging in deep thought. It's a very brittle strain, don't worry. This is normal. It's strong, smokes smooth, and can treat a variety of illness. Love it.”
“Relaxing strain and tastes good”

“It's a pretty strong strain. First thing I noticed was the smell. It's a strong sweet, earthy smell. I decided to take a big hit from the bong. It only takes a couple hits. It leaves a sweet earth taste at the back of your throat. It's a great high. I felt this warm sensation go from my throat and tongue and it spread to my head and down my back. Its a warm, tingly feeling. Its seriously a great high. Your body does ...”

“Great flavor, immediate and then creeping head and body high, feel it in my eyes and head, very relaxed and content. This is a classic heavy hitter just what i went in looking for.”

I did not get dry mouth at all. This strain didn't mess with my head too much, and I was able to enjoy spending time with my boyfriend. I would highly recommend.”

“This was a heavy hitter. It creeped up, then wow. The reviews were not kidding when they said couch lock/trippy high. My MS and osteoarthritis as well as my anxiety went away. At the end of the high I fell into a blissful, long sleep. Will buy again”

As long as you understand that, it’s a 5 star strain.”

“Its colorful and smells sweet. Very easy to break up no grinder needed! Smokes very smooth and gives you a very relaxed feeling then towards the end you feel euphoric. Great for relaxing and watching movies.”

“smell great, excellent choice
very strong”
“Very relaxing strain.”
“I love the calm feeling I get after smoking  cookie kush. Very relaxing and does a great job pushing stress away.”

“Love it! Very relaxing and perfect for having a good time”

“after years of searching for the best strains in Holland, I've came across this strain; which is by far one of the best weed i've have ever smoked. It absolutly kicked in hard, I spaced out in a couple of minutes. Really relaxing and sleepy weed. It will take veteran smokers by supprise.. I absolutly love it”
“This marijuana knocks me on mt a$$ i love it this seems to be one of my top favorites and I'll keep at it.”
“Was a quick but muddled high and not a lot of euphoria but Tired. Iwill try again”

“Very, very good smoke. Smoked one joint before bed and I felt absolutely amazing. I am a fan of the Cookies family but this strain is one of my favorites. If you are looking for a body high but still have the euphoria feeling so you can hold intellectual conversations, this is a perfect choice.”
“Super mellow but uplifting. I'm equally happy watching a movie and organizing my closet. Definitely one of the stronger head highs I've had in a while!”
“slight headache at first... but helps with back and shoulder pain great!”
“At Barney's. Woooonderfull taste! Love it! My TOP-5”

“The combination between 2 amazing strains have made this beautiful and great strain, the high of this one is long, dreamy and very euphoric. It also has a great taste and I would 100% recommend this one.”
